
[1]florid

   FLOR'ID, a. [L. floridus, from floreo, to flower.]

   1. Literally, flowery; covered or abounding with flowers; but in this
   sense little used.

   2. Bright in color; flushed with red; of a lively red color; as a
   florid countenance; a florid cheek.

   3. Embellished with flowers of rhetoric; enriched with lively figures;
   splendid; brilliant; as a florid style; florid eloquence.
